definitions.definition: A plant whose seedling has two cotyledons .
examples: Dicotyledons and monocotyledons together make up the flowering plants, the angiosperms.

definitions.definition: Any plant in what used to be the Dicotyledones .

main_definition: ( botany ) A plant whose seedling has two cotyledons .
secondary_definitions: ( botany , historical ) Any plant in what used to be the Dicotyledones .
